            <physDesc>
              <p>Vellum, about 10 in. by 6 5/8, consisting originally of at least 24
              quires (foll. 153—348), at first numbered from <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܕ</foreign>
              to <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܘ</foreign>, and then from <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܐ</foreign>
              to <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܛ</foreign>, but afterwards, consecutively, from
              <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܒ</foreign> to <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܟܓ</foreign>.
              Leaves are wanting after foll. 246, 283, 284, 285, 347, and 348.
              Each page is divided into two columns, of from 28 to 31 lines.</p>
              <objectDesc form="codex">
                <supportDesc material="perg">
                  <support>
                    <material>Vellum</material>
                  </support>
                  <extent>
                    <measure type="composition" unit="leaf" quantity="196">196 ff.</measure>
